---
import ServicePageLayout from '../layouts/ServicePageLayout.astro';
import { buildProductSchema } from '../lib/schema';

const title = "Pet Urns & Keepsakes | Beautiful Resting Places | Pet Farewell";
const description = "Discover beautiful pet urns, memorial boxes, and keepsakes to honor and preserve the memory of your beloved dog or cat after cremation.";

const headline = "Beautiful Pet Urns & Keepsakes";
const subheadline = "Find a fitting and respectful resting place for your companion's ashes, preserving their memory for years to come.";

const headings = [
  { depth: 2, slug: "choosing-an-urn", text: "Choosing the Right Urn" },
  { depth: 2, slug: "types-of-urns", text: "Types of Pet Urns" },
  { depth: 2, slug: "personalization", text: "Personalization and Engraving" }
];

const faqItems = [
  {
    question: "What size urn do I need for my pet?",
    answer: "A general rule is that you need 1 cubic inch of urn capacity for every 1 pound of your pet's healthy weight. For example, a 50-pound dog would need an urn with at least a 50-cubic-inch capacity."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I transfer the ashes to a new urn later?",
    answer: "Yes. Ashes are typically returned in a sealed plastic bag inside a temporary container or basic urn. You can safely transfer this bag into a new urn whenever you are ready."
  }
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { label: "Pet Cremation", href: "/pet-cremation/", description: "Learn about the cremation process." },
  { label: "Pet Memorial Ideas", href: "/pet-memorial-ideas/", description: "More ways to honor your pet's memory." }
];

const productSchema = buildProductSchema({
  name: "Custom Pet Cremation Urns",
  description: "A selection of high-quality wood, metal, and ceramic urns for pet ashes.",
  url: "https://petfarewell.us/pet-urns/",
  offers: {
    price: 49.99,
    priceCurrency: "USD",
    availability: "https://schema.org/InStock"
  }
});
---

<ServicePageLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  headings={headings}
  faqItems={faqItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  heroImageUrl="/images/pet-urns-hero.jpg"
  heroImageAlt="A collection of beautifully crafted wooden and ceramic pet urns"
  structuredData={productSchema}
>
  <h2 id="choosing-an-urn">Choosing the Right Urn</h2>
  <p>Selecting an urn is a deeply personal decision. The right vessel not only holds your pet's ashes securely but also serves as a beautiful tribute to their life. When choosing an urn, consider where it will be displayed, your personal aesthetic, and the size required based on your pet's weight.</p>

  <h2 id="types-of-urns">Types of Pet Urns</h2>
  <p>There are many styles of urns available to suit different preferences and memorial plans:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Wooden Box Urns:</strong> Classic and warm, often available in oak, cherry, or walnut. Many include a slot to display a favorite photograph of your pet.</li>
    <li><strong>Metal Urns:</strong> Durable and elegant, typically made from brass or pewter, often featuring decorative paw prints or silhouettes.</li>
    <li><strong>Ceramic Urns:</strong> Artistic and unique, these can be displayed as a piece of art in your home.</li>
    <li><strong>Biodegradable Urns:</strong> Designed for families who wish to bury their pet's ashes or scatter them in water. These urns naturally break down over time.</li>
    <li><strong>Keepsake Urns:</strong> Small vessels designed to hold just a tiny portion of the ashes, perfect for families who want to share the ashes among multiple family members.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="personalization">Personalization and Engraving</h2>
  <p>Many urns can be personalized to make them truly unique to your pet. Options often include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Engraving your pet's name, dates of birth and passing, or a short, meaningful quote.</li>
    <li>Attaching a personalized nameplate to wooden or stone urns.</li>
    <li>Choosing an urn that incorporates a cast of your pet's actual paw print.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Take your time in making this selection. Your cremation provider can temporarily hold the ashes in a simple container until you find the perfect resting place.</p>
</ServicePageLayout>
